# Global Project Rules

## Style
- Use TypeScript when adding new business logic modules.
- Use JavaScript only for lightweight browser bootstrap files.
- Prefer functional components and composition patterns.
- Prefer TailwindCSS utility-first styling for new UI work.

## Naming
- Use CamelCase for feature file names (example: `BookingCalendar.tsx`).
- Use PascalCase for UI components and exported component symbols.
- Use lowerCamelCase for functions, variables, and hooks.

## Structure
- Keep source code in `src/`.
- Every component should expose an `index.ts` barrel file.
- Split domain logic by responsibility (`components`, `api`, `hooks`, `types`, `features`).

## Testing
- Use Jest + Testing Library for unit and UI tests.
- Add tests for business logic and edge cases before merge.

## Git
- Follow Conventional Commits (e.g., `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`).
